SUMMARIZER="E">

The Senate panel considering John Tower's nomination as Secretary of Defense has found 
discrepancies in his dealings with defense contractors. The panel members cited differences in his 
testimony before the group and what he wrote in a deposition given at the time of his divorce 
from his second wife in 1987. Tower had told the panel that he only represented British 
Aerospace, Inc. on matters of civil aviation. In the deposition, however, he wrote that he had 
given the company advice on selling certain systems to the defense department. The panel also is 
concerned about Tower's drinking habits and reports of womanizing.</SUM> 

